This ancient symbol is used as a protective amulet by both Jews and Muslims.

The Jewish name, Hamsa, is derived from the Semitic root meaning "five." It is called the Hand of Miriam by Jews named for the prophetess Miriam,elder sister of Moses and Hand of Fatima by Muslims, named for the daughter of Mohammed. 

It is usually worn around the neck or hung on walls or over doors. It is thought to bring blessing and good-luck.


